cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.ITP 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the transmission of information over MIMO channels and analyzes the minimum determinant gains. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of side information in the transmission of messages. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with multicasting messages to multiple users. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with the transmission of multiple messages over MIMO channels. 
5. cs.ITP (Information Theory and Coding) is another possible category as the paper proposes a framework for constructing layered space-time index coding from a class of space-time block codes.
